2026-04-16 12:17:34 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control Input Cable (+) connection', 'Control Input Cable (−) connection'] hypothesis_explanation='Measurements show that at the control module input the cable designated as (+) is at 0 V while the cable designated as (−) is at +12 V, i.e. the two incoming cables from the power supply are swapped. This reversed polarity forward‑biases the inverted‑cables indicator LED (red LED on control module) and also places the control module output node near +12 V on both lines, which is why the load module sees both input terminals at about +12 V and the series diode in the load module never conducts, so the lamp remains off. Correcting the mis‑wiring by swapping the two cables between the power supply module and the control module so that Control Input Cable (+) is actually connected to the power supply positive and Control Input Cable (−) to the negative should restore normal operation.'
