ACTION:
With the 12 V source connected and referenced to the power supply negative, open the control cube and probe: (1) the node at the incoming +12 V from the power supply, (2) the node on the switch input, and (3) the node on the switch output that goes to Control Output Cable (+). Measure voltages at each node with the switch both open and closed, and check continuity of the switch contacts when toggled. Determine whether +12 V is being passed through the switch to the control output when the switch is operated, or if the switch/series trace is open or miswired.
