2026-04-16 12:18:11 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Internal connection between control switch output and Control Output Cable (+)', 'Control Output Cable (+) terminal/port at control module side'] hypothesis_explanation='Measurements show the control input and switch operate correctly at +12 V, and the switch has nominal continuity. Yet the Control Output Cable (+) node is floating/disconnected and remains at 0 V. Continuity tests to the load confirm that the external load cabling is correctly wired to that Control Output Cable (+). This isolates the fault to the internal connection between the switch output node and the Control Output Cable (+) termination (e.g., broken PCB trace, cold solder joint, or miswired lead at that port). Repairing/restoring this internal connection so that the switch output is properly bonded to Control Output Cable (+) should allow +12 V to reach the load when the switch is closed, resolving the remaining fault.'
